author: Rachel Pannett
title: As Mining Drops, Australian State Pivots
text:
MELBOURNE—The Australian state of Victoria has long been this country’s Detroit: a former industrial powerhouse that struggled to cope with a global shift toward cheaper manufacturing centers in Asia and elsewhere.
Now, the state known best abroad for hosting the Australian Open tennis games and Formula One races is rushing to replace workers laid off by traditional manufacturers with high-tech jobs. The efforts mark a nascent shift...
